"title": "4948: hour",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4948: hour",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>One twelfth of the period of daylight between sunrise and sunset. Measurement of time in biblical days was often approximate, referring most frequently to the broad divisions of time marked by the third, sixth and ninth hours. The term also denotes a significant or appointed moment or period of time, especially the hour of Jesus Christ's suffering and his return.</p>\n<h2>Hour as a period of time</h2>\n<h3>A measured interval</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:9\">JHN 11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:9-Matt20:12\">MAT 20:9–20:12</a> <em>The working day lasted twelve hours</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:59\">LUK 22:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:34\">ACT 19:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:1\">REV 8:1</a></p>\n<h3>Symbolising a brief time</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:27\">MAT 6:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:25\">LUK 12:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40\">MAT 26:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:37\">MRK 14:37</a>REV <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark17:12\">17:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:10\">REV 18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:17\">REV 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:19\">REV 18:19</a></p>\n<h3>Symbolising a significant period</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:12\">ECC 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:53\">LUK 22:53</a> <em>Darkness provides an hour of opportunity for the powers of evil.</em></p>\n<h2>Hours denoting specific times of day</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:3-Matt20:5\">MAT 20:3–20:5</a> <em>The third, sixth and ninth hours marked the principal divisions of the day.</em></p>\n<h3>The third hour: 9 a.m</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:25\">MRK 15:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:15\">ACT 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>The sixth hour: noon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:16\">GEN 43:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:27\">1KI 18:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:14\">JOB 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:45\">MAT 27:45</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:44\">LUK 23:44</a></p>\n<h3>The ninth hour: 3 p.m</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:1\">ACT 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:30\">ACT 10:30</a></p>\n<h3>Midnight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:4\">EXO 11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:62\">PSA 119:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:6\">MAT 25:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35\">MRK 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a></p>\n<h3>Other hours of the day</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:52\">JHN 4:52</a> <em>the seventh hour: 1 p.m</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:39\">JHN 1:39</a> <em>the tenth hour: 4 p.m</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:6\">MAT 20:6</a> <em>the eleventh hour: 5 p.m.</em></p>\n<h3>A particular unnamed time of day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:13\">MAT 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:28\">MAT 15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:14\">LUK 22:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:33\">ACT 16:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:13\">REV 11:13</a></p>\n<h2>Hour as an appointed time in God's purpose</h2>\n<h3>The hour of Jesus Christ's suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:23-John12:24\">JHN 12:23–12:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:45\">MAT 26:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:41\">MRK 14:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35\">MRK 14:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:27\">JHN 12:27</a></p>\n<h3>The unexpected hour of Jesus Christ's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:42-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:42–24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:39-Luke12:40\">LUK 12:39–12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:13\">MAT 25:13</a></p>\n<h3>The time before Jesus Christ's return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:11\">ROM 13:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:18\">1JN 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>The hour of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:7\">REV 14:7</a></p>",
